latestPosts.caption:
Pandal Hopper 119... The Days Of Mother... Nine Days Of Navratri... The Nine Days Of Durga Puja... They Are Just Not Merely Days Or A Period Of Festival... It Is A Time When Many Of Us Get Relief And Feel The Burden Of The Unforgiving Life Off Our Chest... 

It Is The Time When Mother Comes To Her Distressed Children And Gives Them Some Relief... A Reason To Continue Their Life And Something To Smile... It Is A Feeling That Makes Us Connect To The Mother Enternal... Like She Is Taking The Head Of Her Child On Her Lap... Comforting The Child That Its Okay And She Is There... The Tears Of Pain And Joy Which Comes Out Of The Eyes... The Overwhelming Happiness That We Feel By Seeing Mother Among Us... Holding On To The Faith... That She Shall Remove The Obstacles Of Our Life...Get Rid Of The Blues And Fill Our Life With Peace And Joy... 

The Nine Days Of Mother's Homecoming Means A Lot To The People In Pain...In Grief... As They Find Comfort... Love... And Blessings At The Feet Of Maa Durga... To Express Their Devotion And Dedication To The Mother Enternal... It Is What Makes The Nine Days So Special... So Desired... As They Are The Days Of Mother... Jai Maa Durga 🙏🙏
